During the Ebola outbreak in 2014 the use of misoprostol, a drug that can be used to self-induce abortion, went up. Misoprostol is prevalent in Sierra Leone and often used by women and underage girls, it is widely sold in pharmacies, stalls and on the black market.

On 8 October Sierra Leone will celebrate the Think Equal day. Sierra Leone joined Think Equal on 20 August and it's first Think Equal Training took place on 29 September with the professors and students at Fourah Bay College (FBC) University of Sierra Leone. Representation by Ministry of Health and the Mayor of central Freetown are expected to attend.

Take action after the Ebola outbreak now to ensure your health after the Ebola outbreak

Now comes the time for action. A just completed international Expert Group Report, and UN interagency report both identify that Equitable, Urgent, Durable and Universal actions now are required by city, district and country health and development stakeholders and can be achieved by them, to rapidly reduce the growing burden of chronic disease now.
